    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-22T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-22T06:00:00-05:00" n="8"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13940: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-22T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 22, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—7:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. According to today’s <hi rend="italic">North China Star</hi>, General Sung
                    Che Yuan<note n="24" xml:id="d8fn24">Chairman of the Hopei-Chahar Political
                        Affairs Council.</note> issued an order at Tientsin yesterday to various
                    military and administrative offices in Hopei and Chahar directing that they (1)
                    refrain from internal warfare, (2) resist all foreign aggression, and (3)
                    annihilate all Communists and bandits. Report states Sung informed subordinates
                    that suppression of bandits and Communists is not to be regarded as internal
                    warfare. In a separate manifesto to soldiers of the 29th Army General Sung
                    admonishes them to (1) support the unification of the country and carry out the
                    orders of the Central Government, (2) safeguard the three important attributes
                    of a sovereign state, namely, sovereignty, land and the people, (3) exterminate
                    Communism.</p>
                <p>2. No broadcasts from Sian have been heard for 4 or 5 nights. Information of
                    value concerning the exact military position in Sian, Kansu, and the exact
                    relationship between Yang Hu Cheng and Yu Hsueh Chung on the one side and the
                    Communist armies on the other is extremely hard to obtain in Peiping. Many hold
                    to the belief that the situation may yet be settled by negotiation and that no
                    major military operations will occur. The trend in China definitely is in the
                    direction of doing away with internal warfare as far as possible.</p>
                <p>By mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
